## Frontend IndexedDB Schema (`TechnoPathDB` — Dexie.js)

The frontend PWA mirrors the server data in an IndexedDB database for offline-first operation. Schema version 2 contains 23 object stores matching the backend tables plus a `sync_meta` store:

| Object Store | Indexed Fields | Server Source |
|-------------|---------------|---------------|
| `facilities` | `id`, `code`, `map_svg_id`, `is_deleted`, `is_active` | `/api/facilities/` |
| `rooms` | `id`, `facility_id`, `code`, `map_svg_id`, `floor`, `is_deleted`, `is_active` | `/api/rooms/` |
| `departments` | `id`, `code`, `is_active` | `/api/core/departments/` |
| `navigation_nodes` | `id`, `map_svg_id`, `node_type`, `floor`, `is_deleted`, `is_active` | `/api/navigation/nodes/` |
| `navigation_edges` | `id`, `from_node_id`, `to_node_id`, `is_deleted` | `/api/navigation/edges/` |
| `map_markers` | `id`, `facility_id`, `room_id`, `marker_type`, `is_active` | `/api/core/map-markers/` |
| `map_labels` | `id`, `is_active` | `/api/core/map-labels/` |
| `faq_entries` | `id`, `category`, `keywords`, `is_deleted` | `/api/chatbot/faq/` |
| `ai_chat_logs` | `id`, `mode`, `created_at` | Local only |
| `notifications` | `id`, `type`, `is_read`, `source_color`, `created_at` | `/api/notifications/` |
| `notification_types` | `id`, `name`, `is_active` | `/api/core/notification-types/` |
| `notification_preferences` | `id`, `user_id`, `notification_type_id` | Local only |
| `feedback` | `id`, `category`, `synced`, `created_at` | Local + sync |
| `ratings` | `id`, `facility_id`, `room_id`, `category`, `is_active`, `created_at` | Local + sync |
| `feedback_flags` | `id`, `rating_id`, `status`, `created_at` | Local only |
| `search_history` | `id`, `query`, `created_at` | Local only |
| `app_usage` | `id`, `user_id`, `session_date` | Local only |
| `usage_analytics` | `id`, `event_type`, `screen_name`, `created_at` | Local only |
| `admin_audit_log` | `id`, `action`, `entity_type`, `created_at` | Local only |
| `users` | `id`, `username`, `user_type`, `is_active` | Local only |
| `device_preferences` | `id`, `user_id`, `device_id` | Local only |
| `app_config` | `id`, `config_key` | `/api/core/app-config/` |
